{
  "stem": "3848.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we used to go to synagogue [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and be with the family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My father used to play the violin, I remember, and sort of left all the five children with my mother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she had to care for us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And that was life before the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when the war started-- 1939, September 1939, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] there was a big change.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just before the war started, we heard all the speeches that Hitler used to give.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was unrest in the cities all around us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't have a radio.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we used to gather in some houses where they had a radio just to listen to his speeches.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we knew that something bad is coming, but we couldn't understand it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We started-- the government, the Polish government-- started to build trenches, get ready for the war because Hitler was threatening the Polish government with all kinds of things.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I remember a case when just before the war, before 1939, there was a Madame Pristerover, which brought in a law not to have kosher-- kosher meat in Poland.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they restricted of the killing of cows and chickens in the kosher ways.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That means in the slaughterhouses.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I remember when the Jews didn't eat meat for-- for months just because of that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were trying to do things that should interfere with the internal politics of Poland just to make trouble.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
